a_5.informal problem:
For a function $P(x, y)$ defined as follows:

$P(x, y) =
\begin{cases}
  1 & \text{if}\ y > x + \frac{1}{4} \\
  0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$

where $0 \leq x \leq 1$ and $0 \leq y \leq 1$, compute the positive integral of the function $P(x, y)$ over the domain. The final answer is $\frac{9}{32}$.
